This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with automatic segmentation of abdomen organs using medical imaging. The use of deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNN), also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of a novel adversarial shape learning objective function may indicate that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.MS) sub-category as well. Finally, the use of medical imaging may suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
